5: Hey, guys. Did you miss me?
8:
Clarita?! What are you doing back
so early? You should still have some
vacation days left!
10:
I figured I'd drop by and hand
everyone their souvenirs.
13:
So... Since I'm here anyway, I should
probably wrap up the stuff I was
working on before I left.
16:
Ah! Actually, we already finished
that for you!
20:
...Wow, you're on top of things. Guess
I'll run a check of our new location
data—
23:
You don't have to worry about that!
We'll take care of it later!
25:
You should make the most out of
your vacation! We'll hold the fort
while you rest.
34:
I'm happy that they've grown
enough to handle things without me.
38:
Really sets my mind at ease while
I'm off duty.
41:
But now I've got all this unexpected
free time that I don't know what to
do with.
53:
I wasn't lying when I said I was
happy though. Me and them—we
grew up in similar circumstances.
55:
I couldn't be more proud to see
them coming into their own and
feeling like they belong there.
58:
But I guess if they don't need my
help anymore, then I...
62: Ugh, no, I can't even say it out loud.
71:
Sounds like blasting powder was
used, which means... that wasn't an
accident.
75:
C-Clarita! Please, help us! There's a
ton of explosions going off in our
district, and we don't know what to
do!
80:
We've got troubleshooters headed
to the sites, but there's too much
information to keep track of... All the
data's getting mixed up!
83:
Oof... Yeah, no way I can sort this
much on my own. In that case...
87:
Okay, everyone, calm down! Take a
deep breath and look at me.
90:
Operators, each of you will manage
one troubleshooter out in the field.
Focus only on the intel in your area.
93:
You guys'll consolidate the data and
share only what each person needs
to know. You're good at that, yeah?
99:
I'll guide while you drive. Pick up your
partner on the way, will you?
105: You should say that to Nate, not me.
110:
Stella, could you watch over some
screens for me? I'm gonna need a
hand to check them all.
122:
Keep your heads cool and trust your
instincts.
125:
We'll make these guys regret
messing with us.
132:
Phew... We captured the criminals
and saved all the victims, too...
140:
Didn't I tell you not to go too wild?
Luckily everything worked out in the
end.
142:
We even made it to the top of the
rankings for emergency rescues.
Our heroes really are the best of the
best.
145:
Thanks for giving it your all, guys. I
knew I could count on you.
147:
...Since I had to cut my vacation
short for this, I can take a bit more
time off, right?
150:
No, you can't! We've been barely
keeping afloat without you!
152:
I hope you'll come back soon. It's
hard to be motivated without
hearing your voice...
155:
...You should really be motivated
with or without me.
157:
Now come on, that's enough horsing
around. Don't burn the place down
while I'm gone, you hear?
160:
Sheesh... They really grew up in the
blink of an eye.
168:
Don't say it straight like that. You're
embarrassing me.
175:
I thought I could take it easy. It's not
like I'm the type that likes taking
care of others...
178:
But... I guess I can look after them a
bit longer.
180:
Gotta protect my home away from
home, after all.
